# Deny by default. The build context is an allowlist, not a blocklist.
#
# The old blocklist could only exclude the noise we happened to think of, which
# meant the image was a function of whatever was lying around in a developer's
# working tree. Anything new — a scratch dir, a log, a local tool's output, an
# editor's dotfiles — silently joined the build context. Now nothing enters
# unless it is named below, and the Dockerfile names again, explicitly, what it
# copies out of it.
*

# Build definition
!gradlew
!gradlew.bat
!settings.gradle.kts
!build.gradle.kts
!gradle.properties
!gradle

# Sources + the config the image ships (the Dockerfile picks the exact files)
!config
!core
!schema
!generators
!formats
!destinations
!inspector
!cli

# ...minus generated output inside those directories
**/build
**/bin
**/.gradle
